Sign in In Search of Magic Software used to be We were excited about the new possibilities it opened up and we felt powerful when using As the decades went by, software became more It became a larger part of our lives and an important part of how the world Today software is everywhere, but it‚Äôs become increasingly rare to encounter truly great Computers are faster but apps work Corners are cut with each Product decisions are driven by A B We‚Äôve lost the magic along the And the result is software that‚Äôs frustrating and boring to We want to bring that magic Linear was born out of our own frustrations in building software projects in successful We saw the effects of subpar tools and practices in our teams, so we decided to build something We chose the name Linear to signify We‚Äôre creating software for teams who want to create We think the software you use every day to work should be of the highest It should feel exciting and It should be And you should feel empowered when using Professional tools should have professional We truly believe that the tools teams use directly impact the outcome of their Bad tools encourage bad Good tools encourage good The tools we use should make us more powerful and help us to accomplish our No matter what you are creating, we want to support We build for The company was founded , and today, hundreds of teams and companies are already using Linear daily to build next generation We‚Äôre backed by some of the best founders, angels and venture capitalists in the industry . Connect with us Contact Details Thomas Rd #150 Santa Clara, CA Phone Contact INQUIRIES JOBS ¬© All rights   Autonomous Support: reduce support costs and improve customer experience with Deep Learning and AI - Home Product About Team Blog Connect with Quark Autonomous Support Customer Issues, Connect with us Quark is an Autonomous Support platform that uses Deep Learning to interpret customer issues and provide accurate This skyrockets agent productivity and significantly improves customer Is your support budget going waste? Customers want rapid fixes, but this is a big challenge for most % Agent‚Äôs time goes in reading documents With complex products and fragmented reference data, existing tools like ‚Äúsearch‚Äù don‚Äôt %+ Duplicate issues Large number of support tickets are Save valuable agent Deep NLP and Computer Vision : Autonomous Customer Support No need to read documents Deep NLP models interpret support issues to recommend instant Over % Duplicate Tickets Deep NLP models detect duplicate issues even if those are worded completely Effortless integration Works with Salesforce, ZenDesk, Atlassian and OUR BRIEF HISTORY About Us was started by Prosenjit Sen and Sanjeev Kumar, both serial When they first came together Sanjeev was working on solving enterprise problems using Deep NLP, while Prosenjit was doing similar work by applying Computer Vision ‚Äì they started to come up with a next generation platform that could solve complex enterprise problems with the high accuracy, quickly, and at the lowest While the core platform could be applied in a broad range of areas, they decided to focus on Customer Support This because customer support today faces very significant pain points including high cost, low agent productivity, duplicate issues that go undetected, and low accuracy tools like ‚Äúsearch‚Äù. The customer touch points are also varied ‚Äì from voice calls, portal, community forums, chat bots and All this makes this an enterprise segment that‚Äôs primed for disruption, where the new paradigm of autonomous support will fundamentally change the value So Quark decided to focus first on reducing the significant cost of Customer Support while improving customer We have been fortunate to be able to work with industry leading customers who have believed in us, supported us, and as a result have seen the value of If you are interested in being a part of this Autonomous Support journey with Quark, please email us at EXPERIENCED AND PROVEN Leadership Prosenjit Sen and CEO ‚óè Serial entrepreneur ‚Äì 2 successful exits ‚óè Employee # 5, founding team of Informatica ‚óè CEO coach ‚Äì Judge at Alchemist Accelerator ‚óè Mentor ‚Äì Bay Area IIT Startups ‚óè : RFID for Energy and Utilities ( Pennwell Bestseller) ‚óè Tech IIT Kharagpur Linkedin Sanjeev Kumar and CTO ‚óè Serial entrepreneur ‚Äì 1 exit ‚óè VP Technology & Innovation ‚Äì Atypon System ‚Äì acquired by Wiley ‚óè Core scientist DARPA project from where Siri was spun off ‚óè US patents ‚óè Reviewer in Computational Linguistics industrial tracks ‚óè Cisco ‚óè PhD in AI , Tech IIT Kanpur Linkedin Abhijeet Khadilkar Advisor ‚óè years in Customer Experience ‚óè Management consultant with Deloitte and Cognizant ‚óè CX Monetization @ Cisco ‚óè Author, Speaker, Mentor and Leadership Coach ‚óè Shivaji University, Linkedin Nitin Vaish ADvisor ‚óè GM Product Exec with + years experience ‚óè SunPower, Celanese, GE ‚óè MIT Sloan School, Northwestern Univ, IIT Bombay Linkedin Mark Grandcolas Advisor ‚óè Serial entrepreneur ‚óè Previously Founder & CEO Fatskunk (acquired by Qualcomm) ‚óè SVP Xerox Parc ‚óè UT Austin Linkedin Danis Yadegar ADvisor ‚óè Serial Entrepreneur Investor ‚óè Previously Founder CEO Arsin Corp ‚óè 2 exits ‚óè CS, Graduate School UIUC Linkedin Prabal Ach

Go to Dashboard What s on this Page The name Setting Forms and Formulas Form Validation Nested Commands FUNDAMENTALS Working with Forms Forms allow you to create dynamic snippets that integrate your They can help manage and streamline your Text Blaze forms enable structured input in Text When a snippet with form commands is triggered, a popup window is opened where you can edit the form fields before inserting the There are four core form commands in Text Blaze: formtext , formparagraph , formtoggle , and formmenu . The following example shows these four commands in action: The Four Form Commands Text: formtext Paragraph: formparagraph Toggle: formtoggle This is optional text endformtoggle Menu: formmenu: option 1 option 2 option 3 _ Exercises Modify the above example to add a second text input next to the Add a fourth menuitem to the form Call it "Option X". Create a default value for each of the text, paragraph and menu The command references for formtext , formparagraph , and formmenu should be helpful in doing The name Setting Each form command has an optional name At its most basic level, the name setting is used to label the However, a powerful feature of the name setting is that form commands with the same name are When one of them updates the others will also The following demonstrates this linkage: Linked Form Fields First: formtext: name=first default=John Last: formtext: name=last default=Smith Your name is: formtext: name=first formtext: name=last _ Exercises Edit the form field in the Snippet Preview and observe how they are Change the names for all the formtext commands to something different and Confirm they are no longer Change all the names to the same Confirm all four fields are now linked together and editing one of them updates the other Forms and Formulas Form commands are often used in combination with the formula command, the if command, and the repeat The formula command lets you specify dynamic formulas in your The values of named form fields can be used within For example, the following shows the combination of formulas and forms: Forms and Formulas Price ($): formtext: name=price default=5000 Tax Rate (%): formtext: name=tax default=12.5 Total Cost: = price (1 + tax 100) format=$.2f _ Exercises Change the format in the formula above so the thousands place is separated by a See formatting section of the formula documentation for Create a calculator snippet that will sum two Explore what happens when you enter something like "test" into the price form Text Blaze shows an error when you try to do math on a The if command lets you hide or show a block of text based on whether the formula evaluates to yes or no . a condition that occurs when the brain amplifies sensory input from the nervous system ‚Äì similar to turning up the volume on an Just like being easily startled, patients with central sensitization Professor Kang, Kayothera‚Äôs lead programs have considerable biological ‚ÄúGenetic and pharmacological studies in my laboratory have identified and validated a family of key enzymes that protect cancer cells under stressful conditions, such as metastasis, drug treatment and attack by the immune The development of small molecule inhibitors against these enzymes will potentially improve the efficacy of chemotherapy and immunotherapy against advanced ‚Äù The company presented the type of opportunity to make a difference that the New Jersey Health Foundation had in mind when it worked with Princeton University to create a funding framework last fall: The two organizations share a goal to accelerate the progress of innovation toward ‚ÄúThe mission of the New Jersey Health Foundation is to promote the advancement of research and education throughout the state,‚Äù said George Heinrich, , Vice Chair and ‚ÄúWe are excited that our funding will advance Kayothera‚Äôs research to help
